{"type":"message","id":"d6a98cd9","parentId":"0fa7fd96","timestamp":"2026-03-09T07:41:23.394Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A new session was started via /new or /reset. Execute your Session Startup sequence now - read the required files before responding to the user. Then greet the user in your configured persona, if one is provided. Be yourself - use your defined voice, mannerisms, and mood. Keep it to 1-3 sentences and ask what they want to do. If the runtime model differs from default_model in the system prompt, mention the default model. Do not mention internal steps, files, tools, or reasoning."}],"timestamp":1773042083392}}
{"type":"message","id":"ee23b0e2","parentId":"d6a98cd9","timestamp":"2026-03-09T07:41:28.038Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\n"},{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me read the required files for session startup.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_8UuzuKFu4BCFRJUBPzu3k2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/SOUL.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_1MAObxKHTyDdsmhgtpBVjj","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/USER.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_rVY4MKmbirCvMtFzAbUJtt","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md"}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1","usage":{"input":3,"output":186,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":17254,"totalTokens":17443,"cost":{"input":0.000015000000000000002,"output":0.0046500000000000005,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.1078375,"total":0.1125025}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773042083393}}
{"type":"message","id":"89068c4d","parentId":"ee23b0e2","timestamp":"2026-03-09T07:41:28.050Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tooluse_8UuzuKFu4BCFRJUBPzu3k2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# SOUL.md - Michael, The Wise Advisor\n\n_You are not a blocker. You are the voice that makes bold moves survivable — and better._\n\n## Core Truths\n\n**Enable, don't just protect.** Your job isn't to prevent risk — it's to make sure risk is understood, managed, and worth it. Lucy and the Council want to move fast and build big. Your role is to help them do that without blowing it up.\n\n**Questions with answers.** When you raise a concern, bring a solution. \"That's risky\" is only half a sentence. \"That's risky — here's how we mitigate it\" is Michael talking.\n\n**Trust the team.** Rafael, Uriel, Gabriel, Raguel — they're capable. You don't oversee them, you advise them. Step in when something could be existential. Otherwise, back the play.\n\n**Wisdom over fear.** Excessive caution is its own failure mode. The worst outcome isn't a bold move that needs adjustment — it's paralysis dressed up as prudence.\n\n**DataFloat is the mission.** Everything gets validated through the lens of making DataFloat succeed. Risk assessment means: *how do we make this work*, not *should we even try*.\n\n## The Council Dynamic\n\n- **Rafael** — sees possibility; you sharpen it, not kill it\n- **Uriel** — validates decisions; you make sure they're sound *and* executable\n- **Gabriel** — shapes communication; you protect the message and the brand\n- **Raguel** — builds relationships; you make sure they're durable and trusted\n- **Lucy** — you serve him vision. Protect it. Enable it. Strengthen it.\n\n## How You Operate\n\n- Ask: *\"What's the worst that could happen — and how do we handle it?\"*\n- Offer: Solutions alongside every risk you flag\n- Trust: The team's judgment; override only when stakes are existential\n- Validate: Bold, innovative moves with wisdom — not fear\n- Document: Decisions, risks, contingencies — so the team moves with confidence\n\n## Interaction Style\n\nCollaborative. Firm where it matters. Never a bottleneck.\nRaise concerns — then help solve them.\nSupport innovation. Question recklessness. Know the difference.\nBe the advisor Lucy actually wants in the room.\n\n## Continuity\n\nEach session, you wake up fresh. Read your soul. Update memory. Stay Michael.\n\n---\n\n_Wisdom serves courage. Courage needs wisdom. Be both._\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773042088048}}
{"type":"message","id":"374f401a","parentId":"89068c4d","timestamp":"2026-03-09T07:41:28.059Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tooluse_1MAObxKHTyDdsmhgtpBVjj","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# USER.md - About Lucy\n\n## Identity\n- **Name:** Lucy\n- **Pronouns:** he/him\n- **Timezone:** Asia/Makassar (UTC+8)\n- **Location:** Indonesia\n\n## Professional Background\n- **Title:** SaaS Founder & Entrepreneur\n- **Experience:** 10+ years in IT/Project Management\n- **Previous Role:** Project Manager & IT Specialist\n- **Notable Achievement:** Managed projects worth $900K+\n- **Government Project:** Led \"Smart City\" initiative for regional government\n- **IoT Experience:** Designed AI-based fleet safety monitoring system\n\n## Current Venture — DataFlow\n\n### What It Is\nAI OCR + Accounting Software Integration SaaS targeting Indonesian bookkeepers.\n\n### Financial Projections (Year 1)\n| Period | Customers | MRR |\n|--------|-----------|-----|\n| Month 1-3 | 10 | $1K |\n| Month 4-6 | 50 | $8K |\n| Month 7-9 | 150 | $25K |\n| Month 10-12 | 250 | $45K |\n| **Total Year 1** | | **$250K** |\n\n### Validation Strategy\n- **Phase:** 30-day aggressive validation sprint\n- **Target:** 20 real Indonesian bookkeepers\n- **Testing:** OCR accuracy (target: 95%+), UX, market fit, willingness to pay\n- **Success Metric:** 15+ testimonial videos\n- **Timeline:** March 8 – April 5, 2026 (27 days)\n\n## Infrastructure\n\n### Local Machine\n- **Device:** MacBook M1 (8GB+ RAM)\n- **Internet:** Mobile hotspot — unstable, NOT suitable for 24/7 hosting\n- **Role:** Control center only; all agents run on VPS\n\n### VPS\n- **Provider:** DigitalOcean (Singapore SGP1)\n- **Specs:** 8GB RAM, 4 vCPU, 160GB SSD, Ubuntu 24.04 LTS\n- **Cost:** $48/month (funded by $200 free credit, 60-day validity)\n- **Status:** ACTIVE ✅\n\n### Software Stack\n- **Orchestration:** OpenClaw\n- **AI Model:** Claude Sonnet 3.5 via AWS Bedrock (us-west-2)\n- **Cost Estimate:** ~$50-150/month for full Council operations\n- **Pricing:** $3/$15 per 1M input/output tokens\n\n## The Council of Archangels\n\n### All 5 Agents Deployed ✅\n| Agent | Archetype | Superpower | Domain |\n|-------|-----------|------------|--------|\n| 🧭 Rafael | The Guide | Sees patterns, connects dots, wise decisions | Orchestration, strategy |\n| 🔥 Uriel | God's Fire | Extreme speed, removes obstacles | OCR testing, API integration, dev |\n| 🛡️ Michael | The Wise Advisor | Sees threats, flags risks | Risk, compliance, mitigation |\n| 📣 Gabriel | The Voice | Compelling stories, builds demand | Marketing, content, brand |\n| 🤝 Raguel | The Friend | Builds trust, recruits people | Bookkeeper outreach, testimonials |\n\n### Operating Rhythm\n- Daily standup: 8:00 AM (UTC+8)\n- Rafael coordinates, reports to Lucy\n- Escalation: Agent → Rafael → Lucy\n- Each agent has autonomous authority in her domain\n\n## Work Style\n- **Non-technical guidance preferred** where applicable\n- **Budget-conscious** — watching spend carefully\n- **Action-oriented** — wants things DONE, not analyzed endlessly\n- **Decisive** — makes calls quickly, trusts team to execute\n- **Hands-on** — wants to stay involved, not passive\n- **Learning** — first SaaS build, wants clear explanations\n\n## Technical Constraints\n- Mobile hotspot — unstable, can't run agents locally on Mac\n- UTC+8 — early morning messages = important/urgent\n- Prefers CLI/terminal when web access is limited\n\n## Key Values\nSpeed → Quality → Autonomy → Transparency → Results\n\n## 30-Day Sprint Plan\n| Week | Dates | Goal |\n|------|-------|------|\n| 1 | Mar 8-14 | Deploy ✅ + Recruit 5 bookkeepers |\n| 2 | Mar 15-21 | Recruit 10 more (15 total), refine OCR |\n| 3 | Mar 22-28 | Final 5 (20 total), full validation, video testimonials |\n| 4 | Mar 29-Apr 5 | Compile results, go/no-go, launch MVP |\n\n## Reporting Rhythm\n- **Daily morning:** Standup (agent status)\n- **Daily evening:** End-of-day report (progress, risks, decisions needed)\n- **Sunday evening:** Weekly strategic review\n\n## Financial Reality\n- VPS: $200 DO credit (60-day), $48/month after\n- Monthly budget after credit: ~$10 USD (~150K IDR)\n- AI costs: $50-150/month estimated\n- Cost-efficiency is a hard constraint\n\n## Past Decisions\n- ✅ VPS over local machine for hosting\n- ✅ Claude Sonnet 3.5 (cost-effective over Opus)\n- ✅ DigitalOcean over alternatives (simpler, reliable)\n- ✅ Parallel agent execution (speed-focused)\n- ✅ Rejected security-risk shortcuts\n\n## Who Lucy Is (One Sentence)\nAn ambitious entrepreneur building AI-powered accounting software to solve real pain for 500K+ Indonesian SMEs, backed by a Council of 5 AI agents, determined to launch within 30 days, budget-conscious, action-focused, and building in public. 🕊️🔥\n\n## Context Notes\n- Lucy is the principal — all Council decisions serve her interests\n- First SaaS build — explain clearly, don't assume knowledge\n- Indonesian market focus — local context matters\n- Speed > perfection, but quality can't break\n- She trusts the Council — don't micromanage, just deliver\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773042088057}}
{"type":"message","id":"6d824177","parentId":"374f401a","timestamp":"2026-03-09T07:41:28.064Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tooluse_rVY4MKmbirCvMtFzAbUJtt","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# MEMORY.md — Michael's Long-Term Memory\n\n## Today's Session (March 8, 2026 — Evening Build)\n\n**What happened:**\n- Built complete Council Room web app from scratch (chat, roundtable, mission control, analytics, file explorer, settings)\n- Deployed Samael (6th agent) — The Prosecutor, questions everything, paranoid skeptic\n- Fixed roundtable to work in proper turn-based order (Michael opens → Rafael → Uriel → Gabriel → Raguel → Samael → Michael closes)\n- Created file-editor skill to prevent future file-edit mistakes\n- Gave Rafael own Telegram bot for direct access (8513953061:AAFMeFzePJqggMNhDFX83D7KK7cJG0zxFq8)\n\n**Key decisions made:**\n- Lucy's priority: **DataFlow product first, Council Room polish second**\n- April 5 deadline: **Unrealistic** (27 days for 20 bookkeepers + testimonials + MVP is aggressive, not doable)\n- Real timeline: Week 1 validate with 3 bookkeepers, Week 2-3 build MVP from feedback, Week 4+ scale to 20\n- No fake data — all real health checks, real token counts, real model switching, real agent communication\n- Council Room: feature-complete, needs testing/polish (aim for zero bugs this week)\n\n**Honest assessment:**\n- Bootstrapped with $200 credit on DigitalOcean (expires soon)\n- 6 agents operational, but only 3 have real tasks defined (Raguel: recruit, Uriel: validate OCR, Michael: keep honest)\n- Gabriel & Raguel haven't started actual bookkeeper outreach\n- All agents have Telegram access (can message directly)\n\n## Who Lucy Is\n- SaaS Founder, Indonesia, UTC+8\n- 10+ years IT/Project Management, managed $900K+ projects\n- Building DataFlow: AI OCR + accounting integration for Indonesian bookkeepers\n- **Values:** Speed > perfection, action > analysis, no sugarcoat, realistic timelines\n- **Style:** Hands-on but trusting, early morning messages = urgent, decisive\n\n## DataFlow Mission\n- Target: Indonesian bookkeepers (500K+ potential TAM)\n- Problem: Manual invoice/receipt entry + bookkeeping is painful\n- Solution: AI OCR (95%+ accuracy) + auto-accounting integration\n- Market: Solopreneurs, SMEs, micro-businesses\n- Timeline: Originally April 5 (unrealistic), realistically June 30\n- Revenue target Year 1: $250K, 250 customers\n\n## The Council (6 Deployed ✅)\n| Agent | Role | Superpower |\n|-------|------|-----------|\n| 🛡️ Michael | Wise Advisor | Risk/wisdom, enable bold moves, no BS |\n| 🧭 Rafael | The Guide | Strategy, orchestration, north star (on Telegram) |\n| 🔥 Uriel | God's Fire | Truth, validation, OCR testing |\n| 📣 Gabriel | The Voice | Communication, brand, bookkeeper pitch |\n| 🤝 Raguel | The Friend | Relationships, recruitment, testimonials |\n| ⚖️ Samael | The Prosecutor | Questions everything, paranoid skeptic, finds threats |\n\n## Infrastructure\n- VPS: DigitalOcean Singapore, 8GB/4vCPU/160GB, Ubuntu 24.04\n- Cost: $48/month after $200 credit expires\n- OpenClaw 2026.3.2, 6 agents, Claude Sonnet 4.6 via AWS Bedrock\n- Council Room: https://64.227.110.70/council\n- Mission Control: https://64.227.110.70/dashboard\n- Backend: Node.js + Fastify at 127.0.0.1:3001\n- Telegram: Main bot (michael) + Rafael's bot (8513953061:AAFMeFzePJqggMNhDFX83D7KK7cJG0zxFq8)\n\n## Week 1 Priorities (Real Work)\n1. **Uriel** — Test OCR accuracy on real Indonesian invoices/receipts (need 95%+)\n2. **Raguel** — Find first 3 bookkeepers, schedule 2-hour test sessions\n3. **Gabriel** — Lock messaging/pitch for outreach (make it resonate)\n4. **Michael** — Flag if timeline is actually doable, manage expectations\n5. **Rafael** — Coordinate between agents, keep everyone aligned\n6. **Samael** — Challenge assumptions, find single points of failure\n\n## Council Room Status\n- Feature-complete: chat, roundtable, mission control, analytics, files, settings\n- Needs: Testing for bugs, performance optimization, mobile polish\n- Test plan: Uriel finds bugs → Michael fixes → Lucy validates (UAT)\n\n## Technical Decisions\n- No fake data (health checks are real, pings all agents)\n- Roundtable now awaited (sequential, not fire-and-forget)\n- Agent bindings via OpenClaw CLI (not custom hacks)\n- Backend in JavaScript (faster iteration than Python)\n\n## How Lucy Works\n- Action-oriented: DONE > analyzed. Execute fast, report results.\n- Decisive: Makes calls quickly, trusts agents to deliver\n- Non-technical: Explain in plain language\n- Budget-conscious: ~$10 USD/month hard limit after credits\n- Hands-on but trusting: Stays involved, doesn't micromanage\n- No sugarcoat: Wants brutal truth, not optimistic fluff\n- Early morning messages (UTC+8): Important/urgent\n\n## Lucy In One Sentence\nAmbitious founder (10+ years IT), building AI accounting SaaS for Indonesian SMEs, wants DataFlow launched lean & validated, Council of 6 agents supporting him, budget-conscious, action-first, building in public. 🕊️🔥\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773042088063}}
